"title": "7459: tabernacle, in OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7459: tabernacle, in ot",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A prefabricated portable structure that was used for worship from the wilderness period until Solomon built the Jerusalem temple.</p>\n<h2>The tabernacle was the place of God's presence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:9-Exod33:10\">EXO 33:9–33:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8\">EXO 25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:34-Exod40:35\">EXO 40:34–40:35</a></p>\n<h2>The construction of the tabernacle</h2>\n<h3>It was built at God's command</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:9\">EXO 25:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:40\">EXO 25:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:32\">EXO 39:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:43\">EXO 39:43</a></p>\n<h3>The materials used in its construction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:3-Exod25:7\">EXO 25:3–25:7</a> <em>Many of these materials were available in the desert. Others, such as gold, would have been obtained from the Egyptians (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:35-Exod12:36\">Ex 12:35–36</a>)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:21-Exod35:24\">EXO 35:21–35:24</a></p>\n<h3>The plan for its construction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:1\">EXO 26:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:7\">EXO 26:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:14-Exod26:15\">EXO 26:14–26:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:26\">EXO 26:26</a></p>\n<h3>The skilled labour employed in its construction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:1-Exod31:6\">EXO 31:1–31:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:30-Exod35:35\">EXO 35:30–35:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:10\">EXO 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:26\">EXO 35:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:1-Exod36:2\">EXO 36:1–36:2</a></p>\n<h2>The tabernacle courtyard and its contents</h2>\n<h3>Its dimensions and construction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:9\">EXO 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:12\">EXO 27:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:18\">EXO 27:18</a></p>\n<h3>The altar of burnt offering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:1\">EXO 27:1</a></p>\n<h3>The laver</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:17-Exod30:18\">EXO 30:17–30:18</a></p>\n<h2>The tabernacle's Holy Place and its contents</h2>\n<h3>Its construction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:36-Exod26:37\">EXO 26:36–26:37</a></p>\n<h3>The incense altar</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:1\">EXO 30:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:5\">EXO 30:5</a></p>\n<h3>The lampstand</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:31\">EXO 25:31</a></p>\n<h3>The golden table for the bread of the Presence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:23\">EXO 25:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:30\">EXO 25:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:35\">EXO 26:35</a></p>\n<h2>The tabernacle's Most Holy Place and its contents</h2>\n<h3>It was separated from the Holy Place by a curtain</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:31-Exod26:33\">EXO 26:31–26:33</a> <em>It was designed as a perfect cube with sides of 10 cubits (4.5 metres).</em></p>\n<h3>It contained the ark of the covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:33-Exod26:34\">EXO 26:33–26:34</a></p>\n<h2>The Levites were responsible for the tabernacle</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:50-Num1:51\">NUM 1:50–1:51</a></p>\n<h2>The non-religious functions of the tabernacle</h2>\n<h3>As a reference point for locating the different tribes in camp</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:1-Num2:2\">NUM 2:1–2:2</a></strong> <em>Symbolising that God was central to the life of the nation.</em></p>\n<h3>The movement of the cloud of glory showed when it was time to make or break camp</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:36-Exod40:38\">EXO 40:36–40:38</a></p>\n<h2>Places where the tabernacle was sited</h2>\n<p>The tabernacle was dedicated at Sinai:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:1-Exod40:2\">EXO 40:1–40:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9-Exod40:11\">EXO 40:9–40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:1\">JOS 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:3\">1SA 1:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:60\">PSA 78:60</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:1\">1SA 21:1</a> <em>Nob</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:39\">1CH 16:39</a> <em>Gibeon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:2-2Chr5:6\">2CH 5:2–5:6</a> <em>Jerusalem</em></p>",
